snippet.textDisplay:
This is not from any scripture, but purely my imagination, as i have dreamt and wished this to happen. And this song connects the story i am going to write - 
On some fine day, after the Kurukshetra war, after establishing dharma in this world, and Pandavas as the rulers, The master of all mysticism - Yogeshwar, Lord Krishna was getting ready to go somewhere. Uddhav ji(Krishna's Charioteer, and student) sees his master being so excited and happy and asks "Hey, madhav where do you intend to go today? Do you intend to go to Pandavas? Or is it Sudama? I shall take you to the place wherever it might be." 
Madhav smiles, "The place u are inquisitive for, I have never left that place even for a while. I have always been there, spiritually. However today, I will go there physically." 

"And what is that place, hey yogeshwar? "

"You shall know it yourself. However you have to go there first and inform the inhabitants about my arrival. I will be going there after a long time" - Krishna replied.

After saying this, Krishna, hands out a message to Uddhav to read it to the inhabitants and instructs the directions of that place. 

Uddhav smiles with tears in his eyes after he understands that his master,  Krishna will be going to Vrindavan ❤. 

Uddhav runs and goes to his chariot and runs the chariots as fast as he can. He is feeling ecstasy, joy, love and bhakti all at one time. He is having goosebumps out of ecstasy.  

He reaches Vrindavan. 

"Who is he? Never seen him here, before" - a gopi asks her friends who were passing by the road, where Uddhav stopped. 

"Do you know, by any chance, where can I find Radha?" - Uddhav asked the gopi. 

"Radha? What work do you have with her? You won't find her here" - Gopi replied.

"Please take me to her, I have something important to tell her" - Uddhav asked the gopi in a serious tone showing an emergency.

"Ok, fine"

Uddhav, the gopi her group goes to the place where Radharani is. The place is more beautiful than heaven. There is a very sweet fragrance everywhere. The place is slightly covered with fog, however it ain't invisible. There is a large garden where one can find flowers of every kind. In the middle there is a big green tree atop a small hill. There are a lot of butterflies over the garden. Rabbits hoping. Burds chirping. With all these, Uddhav is hypnotised. The gopi shakes him and says, pointing towards the big tree - "There, behind the tree, you will find Radha". 
"Could you please take me to her? It will be difficult for me to talk to her alone."
Gopi agrees and takes him to the tree, "Radha, there is someone who wants to meet you".
"Who is it Lalita? Is it my Krishna? If not, tell him to go away." 
"Please accept my greetings. I am Uddhav. I am definitely not your Krishna, however i have been sent by Krishna and there is a message for you from him"

"IS IT?" - a woman, with a beauty that can't be compared to anyone in this universe, with tears flowing out her eyes, with a smile that soothes even fire, came from the back of the tree. "What is it that Krishna has said for me? Hey Uddhav, please tell me". 

All the gopis who were present there, looked at Uddhav with excitement and hope. 

Uddhav said to Radharani - "Your Kanha is coming to Vrindavan today to meet you all".

There is a big pause after this news. Radharani closes her eyes and cries - "You took long, hey govind". She runs towards the center of the village, and cries loudly "Krishna is coming!!!!".

She starts singing this song out of ecstasy. 


Each of the lyrics is a Radharani's asking favour to her Gopi friends, to adorn her, as Krishna is coming.

Tears are coming out of Uddhav eyes and he is thinking "We all love Krishna, adore him, but it is true that our love is just a minute fraction of what Radharani's love for Krishna is" . He folds his hands and bows to Radharani.


(This is completely my own imagination.)
